The paper presents a novel hybrid framework for secure function evaluation (SFE) for machine learning applications. The paper discusses cryptographic protocols and techniques used in the framework, indicating a focus on cryptography (cs.CR). The framework is designed for machine learning applications, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the efficiency and scalability of the framework, indicating a focus on computer communication (cs.CC) and systems and control (cs.SI).
